Licensing for the `pcb` directory
=================================

Unless otherwise noted, all files in this directory and its subdirectories are
licensed under the CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Weakly Reciprocal
(CERN-OHL-W-2.0).

A copy of the CERN-OHL-W-2.0 license text is provided in:
  ./LICENSES/CERN-OHL-W-2.0.txt

Exceptions
----------

The following library files/directories are derived from or include material from
the KiCad official libraries (Copyright the KiCad community), and are licensed
under the Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International license
(CC BY-SA 4.0), with the following exception:

  To the extent that the creation of electronic designs that use 'Licensed
  Material' can be considered to be 'Adapted Material', then the copyright
  holder waives article 3 of the license with respect to these designs and any
  generated files which use data provided as part of the 'Licensed Material'.

Files subject to this license:

  - ./lib/Board43_KiCad.kicad_sym
  - ./lib/Board43_KiCad.pretty/

A copy of the CC BY-SA 4.0 license text is provided in:
  ./LICENSES/CC-BY-SA-4.0.txt

Notes
-----

Use of KiCad library data in the hardware design files in this repository does
not by itself cause the surrounding design files to be licensed under CC BY-SA
4.0. However, redistribution of KiCad library material itself, including modified
versions, remains subject to CC BY-SA 4.0 and applicable attribution requirements.

Where required by CERN-OHL-W-2.0, the Source Location for the Covered Source is
the repository containing this directory, unless otherwise stated in a more
specific notice in an individual file or subdirectory.
